timeline.bodyText:
It's a bit of an anti-pattern to deserialize this and THEN verify it. It's implying that you never want text, filename, targetLang to be null, but it's still possible when you use the regular constructor.
It's probably better to move the verification to the constructor and do something like this instead:
JsonObject json = gson.parseString(jsonStr);
return new OcrTranslateApiMessage(json.get('text'), json.get('filename'), json.get('lang'));

